[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm realizing that class literals can use `getName`, but for member lookups, registration is essential. If an interface method isn't registered, does it lead to a noSuchMethod error? I think I'll need to add library reachability metadata since the library relies on reflection. However, there's an issue because that metadata is currently missing, possibly because the tests didn't adequately cover this aspect. I need to figure out the right approach!
[thinking] 
