if adding tests reveals missing metadata, I should include those. The user mentioned that the uncovered call sites include getMethod, Field.set, and Method.invoke. I wonder if adding metadata for the FinalizableReference method and the Thread field will help Native Image pass. However, the Thread field is private in java.base, and we usually avoid JDK internals. I’ll have to inspect the generated agent.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FPsIiY2xUhNAif0xzQcaq2pm|fc_0ca46a9ec45315950169f5502cfb68819f9b6706c4e26af62e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find build/tests/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0 -maxdepth 4 -type f | sort | head -100 && find tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0 -maxdepth 5 -type f | sort", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find build/tests/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0 -maxdepth 4 -type f | sort | head -100 && find tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0 -maxdepth 5 -type f | sort\",\"timeout\":10}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 890, "output": 1733, "cacheRead": 20992, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23615, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777684497829, "responseId": "resp_0ca46a9ec45315950169f55012ae0c819faf64141eccb9c62c"}}
